Project change log
Date: 2026-03-16

Purpose
- Record the concrete changes made to convert the project into a real-data-only route planning forecaster.
- Document the current model behavior and verified evaluation state.

Main project framing changes
- Removed any planner-training fallback that depended on synthetic or fabricated commercial targets.
- Kept the project honest about the data limitation: no private quote history is present.
- Positioned the planner to train from:
  - real quote history when available
  - real external benchmark history in `market_rate_history` when quotes are unavailable
- Labeled the old stream/dashboard path as a legacy sandbox, not evidence for the real-data planner.

Training and modeling changes
- Reworked the route forecaster from an absolute-price model to a residual-blend model.
- New strategy:
  - start from the latest observed real benchmark cost
  - predict the residual adjustment from that baseline
  - blend the adjustment back into the baseline to reduce overreaction
- Added route-specific interval calibration using a time-based calibration slice instead of relying on narrow quantile outputs from the earlier model.
- Ensured training, evaluation, and future forecast generation use the same prediction path.

Real-data constraints enforced
- No synthetic planner training data is used.
- If `quote_history` is empty, the planner uses real external benchmark history from `market_rate_history`.
- If both `quote_history` and `market_rate_history` are empty, training should refuse.

Files changed
- `app/forecast_support.py`
  - added baseline/residual prediction helpers
  - added residual-blend prediction strategy
  - added interval-width calibration by route
  - updated training metrics to compare against naive benchmark baseline
- `app/forecast_routes.py`
  - switched forecast generation to the shared prediction path
- `ml/evaluate_route_forecaster.py`
  - switched evaluation to the shared prediction path
  - added recent validated 30/60/90 day windows
  - added recent per-route metrics
  - removed deprecated pandas fillna usage
- `app/app.py`
  - softened misleading UI claims
  - marked old UI as legacy sandbox
- `app/stream_engine.py`
  - corrected route encoding mismatch
  - removed random retrain split in favor of time-aware behavior
- `utils/real_data_audit.py`
  - added visibility into `market_rate_history`
- `README.md`
  - updated workflow and honesty rules
  - documented real-data-only planner story
  - documented evaluation command
- Root wrapper scripts added or aligned:
  - `build_forecast_dataset.py`
  - `train_route_forecaster.py`
  - `forecast_routes.py`
  - `evaluate_route_forecaster.py`
  - `sync_public_benchmarks.py`
  - `real_data_audit.py`
  - `compare_external_benchmark.py`
  - `import_quotes.py`
- Support files added:
  - `requirements.txt`
  - `.gitignore`

Verified public-data sync state
- Public benchmark source used by the project: Compass/Xeneta route benchmark history.
- Latest synced benchmark date: 2026-03-13.
- Synced real benchmark history rows in `market_rate_history`: 17780.

Current trained planner
- Model version: 20260316115358
- Training mode: external_benchmark_history
- Training source: Compass/Xeneta
- Prediction strategy: residual_blend

Verified evaluation results on real data
- Holdout:
  - MAE: 211.32
  - RMSE: 414.23
  - MAPE: 8.11%
  - baseline MAE: 224.28
  - baseline MAPE: 8.42%
  - MAE improvement vs baseline: 5.78%
  - interval coverage: 70.36%
- Recent validated windows:
  - last 30 days: MAE 135.56 vs baseline 138.15, MAPE 6.85% vs baseline 7.09%
  - last 60 days: MAE 121.78 vs baseline 125.08, MAPE 6.96% vs baseline 7.08%
  - last 90 days: MAE 116.59 vs baseline 119.55, MAPE 6.81% vs baseline 7.06%

Current forecast output state
- Forecasts generated for 2026-03-30 through 2026-04-05.
- Rows saved for current model version: 56.
- The database still contains older forecast rows for the previous model version on the same forecast date. Those were left in place as history.

Important limitation that still remains
- This is still not direct commercial quote prediction because there is no private quote history in the repository.
- The planner is currently a real-data planning model trained on external benchmark history.
- The latest forward forecast window cannot yet be truth-checked because actual public benchmark data only reaches 2026-03-13.

Commands used for verification
- `python sync_public_benchmarks.py`
- `python train_route_forecaster.py`
- `python evaluate_route_forecaster.py --sync-public`
- `python forecast_routes.py`
- `python real_data_audit.py`
